# React Component Patterns

## Block Components (`src/components/blocks/`)

- Accept all content as **typed props** — never fetch data inside components
- Export a single default function component
- Use shadcn/ui primitives from `@/components/ui/` — don't reinvent them
- Use `cn()` from `@/lib/utils` for conditional class merging

```tsx
// ✅ Good — data-driven, reusable
interface FeaturesProps {
  features: { title: string; description: string; icon: string }[];
}

export default function Features({ features }: FeaturesProps) {
  return (
    <section className="py-16">
      {features.map((f) => (
        <FeatureCard key={f.title} {...f} />
      ))}
    </section>
  );
}
```

```tsx
// ❌ Bad — hardcoded content
export default function Features() {
  const features = [{ title: "Scope Control", ... }]; // Don't do this
}
```

## Hydration Rules

When used in `.astro` pages:
- `client:load` — forms, purchase buttons, mobile nav (needs JS immediately)
- `client:visible` — FAQ accordion, video player, carousel (JS when scrolled into view)
- No directive — static display components (feature cards, hero text, tech stack)

## UI Primitives (`src/components/ui/`)

These come from shadcn/ui via the Mainline template. **Don't modify them directly.** Customize via Tailwind theme tokens in `globals.css` or wrapper components.
